**Design Decisions:**

1. **No `@Refinement` annotations**: The class has no `int` or `double` parameters or return types in any method. All parameters are either object references (`UndoableEdit`) or return types are `boolean`/`String`, which are outside the scope of LiquidJava numeric refinements.

2. **State transitions (`@StateRefinement`):**
   - Constructor transitions to `done(this)` — the initial state has `alive=true, hasBeenDone=true`.
   - `die()` has no `from` constraint because it is callable from ALL states (Done, Undone, Dead all transition to Dead). It transitions `to = "dead(this)"`.
